<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 4: SUPPLEMENTAL DIAGNOSTIC ANALYSIS - FUEL IN COOLANT -
        PROCEDURES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>PROCEDURES</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Plug in block heater to warm coolant.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove fuel return lines at regulator block.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pressurize cooling system to 14 PSI.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Observe fuel return lines, injector bank with fuel to coolant leak will push fuel or air out
                of it's return line.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove injectors on suspect bank.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With cooling system pressurized, observe upper injector sleeve to head fit for leakage (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1252011">4.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After repair, pressurize cooling system to confirm repair.</para>
            <figure id="ef1252011" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1090" filename="../figeg1/EG1090.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.11 Injector Sleeve - Combustion Gas Leak Path</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
